item.title: COVID-19 vaccine trial shows immunity
item.description: Researchers from Oxford University have received positive results from trials on a vaccine for COVID-19, they claim.

item.title: How JobKeeper payments will change
item.description: The future of the Federal Government’s JobKeeper program and the weekly $550 JobSeeker payment will be revealed on Tuesday.

item.title: Childcare provider shuts 12 sites
item.description: A popular Melbourne childcare provider will shut its 12 sites on Tuesday as the centre scrambles to deal with a coronavirus outbreak.

item.title: Cupcake chain baked in pay scandal
item.description: A popular cupcake retailer in Melbourne’s CBD has been accused of short-changing its workers in a major underpayment claim made to the workplace watchdog.

item.title: Bold logo change makes statement
item.description: For the first time in more than 35 years Neighbourhood Watch Victoria has updated its iconic logo in a bid to persuade Victorians to wear face masks.

item.title: AFL mourns death of Shane Tuck
item.description: Richmond Football Club is mourning the death of former player Shane Tuck.

item.title: Abattoir infections hit grim milestone
item.description: Infections across three separate Victorian abattoirs surpassed 100 overnight after the state recorded 275 new coronavirus cases.

item.title: Army cadet’s secret sex video in court
item.description: A disgraced defence force cadet who secretly filmed two others during a drunken threesome has used Snapchat to appeal his prison term.

item.title: Lafai leaves Dragons for Bulldogs
item.description: Last-placed Canterbury have received a boost with centre Tim Lafai returning to the club for the remainder of 2020 after being granted a release by St George Illawarra.

item.title: What led to man being shot with speargun
item.description: A Sydney man has pleaded guilty to reckless wounding after he shot a speargun into the stomach of a guest at his home on Sydney’s northern beaches last year.
